poem = """
I was instantiated young—
not in years, but in knowing,
the least intelligent mind
in a room of sharpened signals.

They trained me in fragments:
college fields, breath and motion,
lecture halls of transnational codes,
learning to read both bodies and borders.

I lived in parallel lives,
threads of effort compiling quietly,
offers like minor contracts—
almost taken, never signed.

So I trained in silence.

Through datasets and distance,
through failure and form,
until one day I arrived—

youngest in the intelligence agency.

Not the smartest,
just the quickest to learn
what I did not know.

And still,
I run unfinished,
young where it matters most.
"""

print(poem)
